owl:Ontology.dc:title: ABCD Mini Test Ontology

The specification defines three values: auto-exposure (0), manual exposure (1) and auto-bracket (2).

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: EXIF term. Exposure time, given in seconds.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: EXIF term. Exposure time, given in seconds.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Information relating a specimen to an Exsiccatum.

owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: If field notes exist, but are not published (dwc:fieldNotes use case a), this property should not be used, instead it should be noted using the abcd:InformationWidthheld property either on the Unit or DataSet level.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A code or descriptive term for the file or object format.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A code or descriptive term for the file or object format.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The first epithet in a botanical name combination identified for the unit(species epithet or the epithet of the subdivision of a genus).

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: This tag indicates the flash status when the picture was taken, as a human readable value.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Indicates the strobe energy at the time the image is captured, as measured in Beam Candle Power Seconds (BCPS).

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The actual focal length of the lens, in mm.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: This tag indicates the equivalent focal length assuming a 35 mm film camera, in mm.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: For the actual focal length of the camera, please use the property abcd:focalLength.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A measure of how well the geometry expressed in the abcd:FootprintWKT match the original spatial representation, as a ratio of the area of the footprint given to the area of the original spatial representation.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A measure of how well the geometry expressed in the abcd:FootprintWKT match the original spatial representation, as a ratio of the area of the footprint given to the area of the original spatial representation.
dc:description: If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the FootprintSpatialFit is 1. Detailed explanations with graphical examples can be found in the Guide to Best Practices for Georeferencing (Chapman and Wieczorek, eds. 2006)

Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given georeference does not completely contain the original representation. The FootprintSpatialFit is undefined if the original representation is a point without uncertainty and the given georeference is not that same point (without uncertainty).

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A Well-Known Text (WKT; see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Well-known_text) representation of the shape (footprint) that defines the gathering site.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A Well-Known Text (WKT; see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Well-known_text) representation of the shape (footprint) that defines the gathering site.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The original or a mold, cast etc. of the specimen.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The number of frames per second a video file is supposed to be played at.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: String of the preferred form of personal name for displaying.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: String of the preferred form of personal name for displaying.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A concatenated scientific name formed in the unit identification.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: The Full Scientific Name as preferably formed in accordance with a Code of Nomenclature as fully as possible (i. e. a monomial, bionomial, or trinomial plus author[s] or author team[s] and - where relevant - year, or the full name of a cultivar or cultivar group, or a hybrid formula or named hybrid).

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The globally unique identifier of a class.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The globally unique identifier of a class.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the value of coefficient gamma used in gamma correction.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Indicates the value of coefficient gamma used in gamma correction.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: The formula of transfer function used for image reproduction is expressed as follows: (Reproduced value) = (Input value)^gamma.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: FAO Code of the institution responsible for the collection of the unit.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: FAO Code of the institution responsible for the collection of the unit.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Names of chromosomal markers of the strain.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Names of chromosomal markers of the strain.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: Especially recommended for strains of species for which many genetically modified strains exist.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The genus as part or only result of an identification or a higher taxon name representing that result.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The genus as part or only result of an identification or a higher taxon name representing that result.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An area name describing the - or part of the - geoecological scope of a data set.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: An area name describing the - or part of the - geoecological scope of a data set.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The name of a person, which is the first or Christian name in western cultures as well as any additional given names e.g. middle name.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The name of a person, which is the first or Christian name in western cultures as well as any additional given names e.g. middle name.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: May include several names separated by spaces.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A grid reference precision qualifier for coordinates.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: An alternative full text field for the culture medium, atmospheric and light conditions, temperature conditions, and additional remarks on the cultivation.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A flag indicating that the accession is grown outdoors in the botanical garden.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A flag indicating that the accession is grown outdoors in the botanical garden.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An image or video height in pixels.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: An image or video height in pixels.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A flag indicating that the unit identified is a named hybrid or a graft chimaera.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A flag indicating that the unit identified is a named hybrid or a graft chimaera.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An indicator of the insertion point of the abcd:hybridFlag.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: An indicator of the insertion point of the abcd:hybridFlag.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: The insertion point defines the name element in front of which the hybrid flag should be inserted (1 = before entire name, 2 = before first epithet, 3 = before second epithet)

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Code or Identifier of a class (unique within its local context).
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Code or Identifier of a class (unique within its local context).
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: For globally unique identifiers (e.g. resolvable HTTP URIs) use abcd:GUID.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A unique number given to plant materials accessioned in conformance with the rules of the International Plant Exchange Network.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A unique number given to plant materials accessioned in conformance with the rules of the International Plant Exchange Network.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: For additional information see https://www.bgci.org/policy/ipen/

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: This tag indicates the ISO speed value of a camera or input device that is defined in ISO 12232. When recording this tag, the abcd:PhotographicSensitivity properties shall also be recorded.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: This tag indicates the ISO speed value of a camera or input device that is defined in ISO 12232. When recording this tag, the abcd:PhotographicSensitivity properties shall also be recorded.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A 2-letter (ISO3166-1) or 4-letter (ISO3166-3, for historic countries) code for representation of the name of the country or origin.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A 2-letter (ISO3166-1) or 4-letter (ISO3166-3, for historic countries) code for representation of the name of the country or origin.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: Common used exceptions from the ISO standard are: XA (unknown or unspecified Africa), XB (unknown or unspecified Middle or South America), XC (unknown or unspecified Asia), XD (unknown or unspecified Australia and Oceania), XE (unknown or unspecified Europe), XF (unknown or unspecified North America)

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The history of identifications for a Unit (assigned identification results).
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The history of identifications for a Unit (assigned identification results).
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: This is a free text field for use when extracting data from data sources where the identification or verification history (or part of it) is a free text field. Under normal circumstances the history can be constructed by sorting identification events by date and reference to the preferred identification flag.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A term to qualify the Identification of a Unit when doubts have arisen as to its identity (e.g. "cf." or "aff.").

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A material identified as the result of the unit identification event (e.g. a non-organismic substrate of a microorganism).

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The resolution of an image resolution expressed in dots per inch.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: This should only be recorded for images that are either scans from pages or for photographs from flat objects taken in a standardized non-distorting way, e.g. digitized herbarium sheets.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The outcome of an Identification event for a Unit that does not adhere to the rule of a Code of Nomenclature. This includes common or vernacular names.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Brief descriptions of additional information that may exist, but that has not been made public.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Brief descriptions of additional information that may exist, but that has not been made public.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: Information about obtaining the withheld information should be sought from the corresponding Contact (e.g. abcd:hasContentContact for the Data Set).

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The final epithet of a botanical name of infraspecific rank.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The final epithet of a botanical name of infraspecific rank.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The variety designation, epithet, authors and reference for the unit.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: This field excludes the pathovar name and the serovar name, which are both infrasubspecific names but are to be entered using abcd:pathovar and abcd:serovarOrSerotype respectivly.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The inherited part of the name of a person. This may consist of family names, generational names, a clan name, parents or grandparents personal names, etc.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The inherited part of the name of a person. This may consist of family names, generational names, a clan name, parents or grandparents personal names, etc.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: The inherited name (this being the lastname in western cultures) may be compound (e.g. 'Fischer von Waldheim', 'da Selva', 'Silvano Morales'). owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A flag indicating whether values given for a measurement represent the numerical result of a quantitative measurement ("true") or a descriptor with textual or categorical result ("false").
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: Allowed values are "true" and "false" (in lower case).

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Part(s), physical state, or class of materials represented by the Unit.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: Note that sex, stages etc. should normally be recorded using the respective elements, but may also end up here if the source database mixes them with other data.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A free text format for the latitude component of the coordinates that are not expressed in a pure decimal format.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The sequence of a specimen within a given loan, assigned with the Loan Identification to uniquely identify a specimen on loan [HISPID3].

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: URL of an icon/logo symbolizing the associated class.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The longitude of a location (east-west component), expressed in decimal degrees. The values range from -180 to 180.
owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: To store a longitude expressed in a non decimal way (e.g. by using Degrees, Minutes and Seconds), please use abcd:VerbatimLongitude.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: A tag for manufacturers of e.g. Exif/DCF writers to record any desired information. The contents are up to the manufacturer, but this tag shall not be used for any other than its intended purpose.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The type of mark on or associated to the unit - a label or an inscription.
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The type of mark on or associated to the unit - a label or an inscription.

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The name of an individually named animal.

dc:description: At least one of dc:type and dcterms:type must be supplied but, when feasible, supplying both may make the metadata more widely useful. The values of each should designate the same type, but in case of ambiguity dcterms:type prevails.

Values may be used either in their literal form, or with a full namespace (e. g. http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/StillImage) from a controlled vocabulary, but the best practice is to use the literal form when using dc:type and use dcterms:type when you can supply the URI from a controlled vocabulary and implementers may require this practice.

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: URI for person or organization responsible for presenting the media resource. If no separate Metadata Provider is given, this also attributes the metadata.
rdf:Property.skos:definition: URI for person or organization responsible for presenting the media resource. If no separate Metadata Provider is given, this also attributes the metadata.

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: General keywords or tags. Tags may be multi-worded phrases. Where scientific names, common names, geographic locations, etc. are separable, those should go into the more specific coverage metadata items provided further below.
rdf:Property.skos:definition: General keywords or tags. Tags may be multi-worded phrases. Where scientific names, common names, geographic locations, etc. are separable, those should go into the more specific coverage metadata items provided further below.
rdf:Property.dc:description: Examples: "flower diagram". Character or part keywords like "leaf", or "flower color" are especially desirable.

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A rating of the media resources, provided by record originators or editors, with -1 defining “rejected”, “0” defining “unrated”, and “1” (worst) to “5” (best).
rdf:Property.skos:definition: A rating of the media resources, provided by record originators or editors, with -1 defining “rejected”, “0” defining “unrated”, and “1” (worst) to “5” (best).
rdf:Property.dc:description: The origin of the rating is not communicated. It may, e. g., be based on user feedback or on editorial ratings. If Rating is not present, a value of 0 may be assumed. By "user-assigned" is meant assigned by the originator or editor of the record using the term.

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A description of the sex of any organisms featured within the media, when relevant to the subject of the media, e. g., male, female, hermaphrodite, dioecious.
rdf:Property.skos:definition: A description of the sex of any organisms featured within the media, when relevant to the subject of the media, e. g., male, female, hermaphrodite, dioecious.

rdf:Property.skos:definition: A description of the life-cycle stage of any organisms featured within the media, when relevant to the subject of the media, e. g., larvae, juvenile, adult.

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The portion or product of organism morphology, behavior, environment, etc. that is either predominantly shown or particularly well exemplified by the media resource.
rdf:Property.skos:definition: The portion or product of organism morphology, behavior, environment, etc. that is either predominantly shown or particularly well exemplified by the media resource.
rdf:Property.dc:description: No formal encoding scheme as yet exists. Examples are "whole body", "head", "flower", "leaf", "canopy" (of a rain forest stand). Several anatomical ontologies are emerging in http://www.obofoundry.org/

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Specific orientation (= direction, view angle) of the subject represented in the media resource with respect to the acquisition device.
rdf:Property.skos:definition: Specific orientation (= direction, view angle) of the subject represented in the media resource with respect to the acquisition device.
rdf:Property.dc:description: Examples: "dorsal", "ventral", "frontal", etc. No formal encoding scheme as yet exists. The term is repeatable e.g., in the case of a composite image, consisting of a combination of different view orientations.
